<span class="pageheading">Mobile computing</span><br>
<span class="generaltext" id="space">

A technology that allows transmission of data, via a computer, 
			without having to be connected to a fixed physical link.<br>
Mobile computing is a generic term describing one's ability to use technology while 
moving, as opposed to portable computers, which are only practical for use while 
deployed in a stationary configuration 
<br>
Mobile 
computing embraces a host of portable technologies that makes Internet access on 
&nbsp;the go not only possible, but integral to everyday life. From notebook 
computers to personal digital assistants to standard cell phones, mobile 
computing has become an indispensable way of life.<a href="app_srv/icmr/gl/formats/Mobile_computing.pdf" target="_blank">read more</a>
